        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(194, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(195, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(196, "img", 28);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(197, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(198, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(199, " Colorado Festival of Horror is thrilled to announce Emmy Award-winning MakeUp FX Artist Dean Gates is coming to our September convention in 10 days! Catch him at his table in the Outworld Bar area as well as at his Q&A in Monster Main Events on Sunday.\nVirginia-born Dean Gates got his start in feature films as a University of Miami intern assisting makeup effects guru Tom Savini on EYES OF A STRANGER (1981). After being a production assistant on Brian DePalma\u2019s SCARFACE (1983), Dean was called back with Savini\u2019s crew on George A. Romero\u2019s DAY OF THE DEAD (1985) and Chuck Norris\u2019s action epic INVASION USA (1985). Dean\u2019s first feature as department head was on NIGHTMARE WEEKEND (1986). After that, he was recruited to work for Italian producer Dino De Laurentiis where he provided mayhem for Stephen King\u2019s MAXIMUM OVERDRIVE (1986), David Lynch\u2019s BLUE VELVET (1986), Arnold Schwarzenegger\u2019s RAW DEAL (1986), and DRACULA\u2019S WIDOW with Sylvia Kristel. He worked for nine months creating ape suits on Carlo Rambaldi\u2019s crew for KING KONG LIVES! (1986). The following year brought Dean to Los Angeles to work for Roger Corman on THE TERROR WITHIN (1989) and TRANSYLVANIA TWIST (1989). Then, back to the east coast for THE RETURN OF SWAMP THING (1989) and Abel Ferrara\u2019s CAT CHASER (1989). After moving full-time to LA, Dean had a great run on horror favorites MANIAC COP 2 (1990), BUFFY THE VAMPIRE SLAYER (1992), and PHANTASM III: LORD OF THE DEAD (1994). Dean won an Emmy Award for his work on STAR TREK: DEEP SPACE NINE (1995) and worked on the effects team that won an Academy Award Oscar for James Cameron\u2019s THE ABYSS (1989). ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(200, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(201, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(202, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(203, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(204, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(205, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(206, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(207, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(208, "img", 29);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(209, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(210, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(211, " Colorado Festival of Horror is hair-raised to announce Guest Author Josh Viola coming to our convention next week Sept 9, 10 & 11! He will be meeting fans and signing books at the Hex Publishers table in the Outworld Bar area all weekend long. Joshua Viola is a 2021 Splatterpunk Award nominee, four-time Colorado Book Award finalist, editor of the StokerCon\u2122 2021 Souvenir Anthology (Horror Writers Association) and Colorado Book Award Best Anthology 2021 winner for Shadow Atlas: Dark Landscapes of the Americas. He is the co-author of the Denver Moon series (Hex Publishers) with Warren Hammond. Their graphic novel, Denver Moon: Metamorphosis, was included on the 2018 Bram Stoker Award\u00AE Preliminary Ballot. Josh edited the Denver Post bestselling horror anthology Nightmares Unhinged (Hex Publishers), and co-edited Cyber World (Hex Publishers)\u2014named one of the best science fiction anthologies of 2016 by Barnes & Noble. His short fiction has appeared in numerous anthologies, including One of Us: A Tribute to Frank Michaels Errington (Bloodshot Books), DOA III: Extreme Horror Anthology (Blood Bound Books), Doorbells at Dusk (Corpus Press), and Classic Monsters Unleashed (Crystal Lake Publishing/Black Spot Books). He is also a regular contributor to Denver\u2019s popular art and culture magazine, Birdy, and has reprints available on Tor.com. Josh is the owner and chief editor of Hex Publishers in Denver, Colorado. Josh co-authored with Sean Eads the short story \u201CThe Devil's Reel\" for the Hex Publishers & COFOH best-selling anthology It Came From the Multiplex: 80s Midnight Chillers. Convention exclusive copies available at the show! ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(212, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(213, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(214, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(215, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(216, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(217, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(218, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(219, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(220, "img", 30);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(221, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(222, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(223, " Colorado Festival of Horror is bone-chilled to announce Guest Author Sean Eads coming to our convention on Friday Sept 9th! He will be meeting fans and signing books at the Hex Publishers table in the Outworld Bar area from 5-6pm. Sean Eads is a librarian and author living in Denver, CO. He is originally from KY. His first novel, The Survivors, was a finalist for the Lambda Literary Award. His third novel, Lord Byron's Prophecy, was a finalist for the Shirley Jackson Award and Colorado Book Award. His fourth novel, The Feast of Panthers, was published in August 2022. His fifth novel, Confessions, will come out in November 2022. You can find him online at seaneads.net.\nSean contributed \"A Nugget of Wisdom\" short story to the 2021 Colorado Book Award-winning Best Anthology Shadow Atlas: Dark Landscapes of the Americas. He also co-authored with Josh Viola the short story \u201CThe Devil's Reel\" for the Hex Publishers & COFOH best-selling anthology It Came From the Multiplex: 80s Midnight Chillers. Convention exclusive copies available at the show! ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(224, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(225, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(226, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(227, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(228, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(229, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(230, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(231, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(232, "img", 31);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(233, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(234, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(235, " Colorado Festival of Horror is thrilled to announcement Special Comic Book Artist Jorge Corona is coming to our September convention! His appearance is being sponsored by Wayne Winsett & Time Warp Comics. Jorge Corona is a Venezuelan sequential artist and the winner of the 2015 Russ Manning Award. A writer and illustrator, his works include horror title The Me You Love In the Dark and Middlewest for Image Comics, We Are\u2026 Robin for DC Comics, and Big Trouble in Little China: Old Man Jack, Adventure Time, and Jim Henson\u2019s The Storyteller: Dragons for BOOM! Studios. Jorge is also the co-creator of Goners and No. 1 With A Bullet (nominated for the 2018 Eisner Award for Best Cover Artist) for Image Comics, and creator of Feathers, his all-ages dark fantasy, for Archaia Entertainment. He is currently working on Batgirls for DC Comics. Jorge lives in Denver with his wife and fellow artist Morgan Beem. Thank you to Time Warp Comics for sponsoring Jorge\u2019s appearance! ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(236, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(237, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(238, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(239, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(240, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(241, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(242, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(243, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(244, "img", 32);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(245, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(246, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(247, " Colorado Festival of Horror is chilled to announce the return of the Rocky Mountain Paranormal Research Society! Bryan Bonner & Bob Lewis are bringing lots of spooky programming to this year's con plus the return of Jigsaw's Horror Trivia and a LIVE podcast with a COFOH Special Guest! You can also find them in the Death Dealers Room. For more than two decades, Rocky Mountain Paranormal has proudly been Colorado\u2019s only forensic paranormal research society, with equal emphases on diligent investigations of paranormal claims and education and outreach programs aimed toward using the framework of paranormal claims to teach as much as possible about science and history. Everyone loves a good ghost story, right? Bryan Bonner has examined a wide range of reported paranormal phenomena, including ghosts, poltergeists, psychics, UFOs, conspiracy theories, urban legends, and much more. Unlike others in the field, Bryan has made sure not to run around cemeteries, screaming and scaring the group with over\u2010active imaginations. From the field to the lab, he tests bizarre beliefs and practices, conducts experiments and on\u2010site investigations, and recreates unusual events. Bob Lewis has an eclectic and interdisciplinary background, an obsession with the weird, an overactive sense of curiosity. He holds degrees in Biology, English, Mathematics, and Psychology (and if that weren\u2019t enough, also took a minor in Astrophysics and then returned to grad school for more) and has a background in interdisciplinary study and research that lends itself well to investigations of unknown or unusual phenomena. Furthermore, he has professional experience in writing and publishing, magic and mentalism, and education. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(248, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(249, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(250, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(251, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(252, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(253, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(254, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(255, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(256, "img", 33);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(257, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(258, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(259, " Colorado Festival of Horror is thrilled to announce award-winning Special Guest Author Mario Acevedo coming to our September convention! Mario will be meeting fans and signing books at the Hex Publishers table in the Outworld Bar area. Mario Acevedo is the author of the national bestselling Felix Gomez detective-vampire series, most recently Steampunk Banditos: Sex Slaves of Shark Island, the graphic novel from IDW, Killing the Cobra, and the forthcoming, Cats In Quarantine: A Cartoon Memoir of the COVID-19 Pandemic. He has also authored the YA humor thriller, University of Doom, and co-authored the Western novel, Luther, Wyoming. His work has won an International Latino Book Award, a Colorado Book Award, and has appeared in numerous anthologies to include Denver Noir, \u00A1El Porvenir, Ya!, Shadow Atlas: Dark Landscapes of the Americas, A Fistful of Dinosaurs, Straight Outta Deadwood, Psi-Wars, and It Came From The Multiplex. Mario was a faculty member of the Regis University Mile-High MFA program and Lighthouse Writers Workshops. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(260, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(261, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(262, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(263, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(264, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(265, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(266, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(267, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(268, "img", 34);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(269, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(270, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(271, " Colorado Festival of Horror is thrilled to announce award-winning Special Guest Authors Angie Hodapp and Warren Hammond coming to our September convention! They will be meeting fans and signing books at the Hex Publishers table in the Outworld Bar area. Warren Hammond has authored several science fiction novels, quite a few short stories, and a graphic novel. His 2012 novel, KOP Killer, won the Colorado Book Award for best mystery. His latest series, Denver Moon, is co-written with Joshua Viola. Angie Hodapp is the Director of Literary Development at Nelson Literary Agency. She holds a BA in English and secondary education from the University of Northern Colorado and an MA in English and communication development from Colorado State University. A graduate of the Publishing Institute at the University of Denver, she has worked in professional writing, editing, and education for more than twenty years. A frequent presenter at writing conferences and events, and the author of Query Craft and Do You Need a Literary Agent, she loves helping writers improve their craft and learn about the ever-changing world of publishing. Warren and Angie contributed the opening short stories \u201CAlien Parasites From Outer Space\u201D and \u201CReturn of the Alien Parasites From Outer Space\u201D to the Hex Publishers & COFOH best-selling anthology It Came From the Multiplex: 80s Midnight Chillers. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(272, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(273, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(274, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(275, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(276, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(277, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(278, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(279, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(280, "img", 35);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(281, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(282, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(283, " Colorado Festival of Horror and sponsors Angela Joseph & Alien Donut Films are excited to announce actor Sheri Davis is coming to our September convention! Sheri will be meeting fans and signing autographs at the Angela Joseph Productions table in the Outworld Bar area. Sheri Davis, actress/producer/director, was born and raised in a small town in Texas. She grew up riding horses and motorcycles. Always a fierce competitor, she was an athlete and honor roll student in high school and earned degrees in psychology and nursing in college. When she began acting, many filmmakers discovered that her talents were being underutilized. Sheri was asked to help produce, cast, and pull together entire films. She's worked on productions as assistant director, script supervisor and production manager. Armed with her knowledge of filmmaking, from the seed of an idea through distribution, Sheri directed her first short film in 2017 titled, Hair of the Dog, which won several awards. She just completed directing the comedic short film 970 Square Feet. Next, Sheri is starting pre-production on Amber Alert which will be the first installment to her anthology. Sheri has also made a name for herself in the independent film world, as a very versatile actor who is not afraid to take on any role, as evidenced by her role as Karma Blake in the award-winning, and controversial short film Snake With A Human Tail, which earned her the title of a \"Scream Queen\" and established a horror genre fan base. Sheri can be seen in other movies such as Blind, Fall of Grace, Till Death, Lake of Shadows, Vengeance Girl, Violence on Demand, Bearry, Cold Blooded Killers, It Wants Blood!, the Alien Danger! film series and the short film, The Lightning Man. Sheri has also received Best Actress Nominations and won 2 Best Actress Awards. Sheri's credits: https://www.imdb.com/name/nm5560956/?ref_=fn_al_nm_1 Special thank-you to Angela Joseph Productions and Alien Donut Films for sponsoring Sheri\u2019s appearance! ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(284, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(285, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(286, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(287, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(288, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(289, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(290, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(291, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(292, "img", 36);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(293, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(294, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(295, "a", 37);
        i0.ɵɵtext(296, "Colorado Festival of Horror");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵtext(297, " is thrilled to announce ");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(298, "a", 38);
        i0.ɵɵtext(299, "The Enigma");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵtext(300, " is coming to our September 2022 convention! The Enigma will be meeting fans, signing autographs, doing professional photo ops and one of the judges for our first-ever ");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(301, "a", 39);
        i0.ɵɵtext(302, "COFOH \"Inked In Blood\" Horror Tattoo Competition at Colorado Festival of Horror!");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelement(303, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(304, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(305, " The Enigma is a legendary performer particularly at music festivals and tattoo conventions. His show is based on circus and tattoo culture which defines pop culture today. Cultivating audiences for over 20 years around the globe, The Enigma has literally changed the face of live entertainment. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(306, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(307, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(308, " A founding member of Jim Rose Circus, The Enigma has toured the world many times over performing at festivals, theaters, and rock venues. i.e. Nine Inch Nails tour of the US, highest grossing show at Edinburgh Fringe Festival two years in a row, opening for David Bowie, etc. Making his Prime Time television debut on the The X Files in 1995, The Enigma has been on many talk shows and breakfast news shows around the world. \"Ripley's Believe It Or Not!\" and Guinness World Records have also carried his image. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(309, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(310, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(311, " Coming from a background of classical piano and stage magic, The Enigma's live show includes the best possible traditional stunts. Being an innovator of the bizarre, The Enigma also produces stunts none have ever seen. All of the original music backing the show and the odd humor allow audiences to breathe and adds to The Enigma as an identifiable character. The Enigma has been on the cover of many tattoo magazines, setting the example for extreme body modification. Featured twice in National Geographic magazine, 1995 and 2004, The Enigma gets hard news stories about his shows published in advance of his debuts. The Enigma has not stopped covering new ground, breaking into the comic book arena as well as monster truck rallies and school anti-bully lectures. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(312, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(313, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(314, " When you think of extreme, wild, out of this world entertainers, The Enigma stands out as the leader of his art form. He is an historic legend in body modification, circus sideshow, and tattooing, and leads the pack in that \u201Cdo it yourself\u201D renaissance style. As a refined talent of over 20 years in the business you can see that he continues to amaze and inspire. The Enigma's cult status and huge following will grow organically over the years as he constantly gives to the art world. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(315, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(316, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(317, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(318, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(319, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(320, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(321, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(322, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(323, "img", 40);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(324, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(325, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(326, "a", 37);
        i0.ɵɵtext(327, "Colorado Festival of Horror");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵtext(328, " and sponsor ");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(329, "a", 41);
        i0.ɵɵtext(330, "Alien Donut Films");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵtext(331, " are thrilled to announce actor ");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(332, "a", 42);
        i0.ɵɵtext(333, "G Larry Butler");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵtext(334, " is coming to our September 2022 convention! G. Larry will be meeting fans and signing autographs at ");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(335, "a", 43);
        i0.ɵɵtext(336, "Bill Victor Arucan");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵtext(337, " & ");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(338, "a", 44);
        i0.ɵɵtext(339, "James Balsamo's");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵtext(340, " Alien Donut Films table in the Outworld Bar area. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(341, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(342, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(343, "\nG. Larry Butler is one of the few actors to work in every phase of the show business industry on a continuous basis: Feature Film, Television, Internet, Radio, Theater, and Concert Hall. He began his film career with the feature film The Women\u2019s Club in 1985. Since then he has been involved in more than 200 projects. Larry has dabbled in almost every aspect of show business, such as Vaudeville, TV news reporter, voice over artist for Japanese animation, audio book narrator, international print character model and commercial artist, concert pianist, award-winning published poet, and host of several TV shows. His most significant was Underground Hollywood in which he simultaneously hosted a radio show and a TV show, interviewing unknown artists of all types: Singers, Musicians, Actors, Authors, etc., shot in an actual cave. Acting for TV and film, his roots are in comedy, but he has crossed over to all other genres as well, most notably horror. He starred as Dr. Lazarof in the international hit Frankenstein vs the Creature from Blood Cove (an homage to the 1930s and 40s classic monster films, which won the grand prize at the World Horror Fest in 2006), and again as Professor Hunter in the very popular PanMan, a comedy horror feature film. Recently he has costarring roles in the horror films Its Just A Game, Hollywood Werewolf, Journey to Hell, Clown Motel 2, the suspense/mystery thriller, The Deceased Won\u2019t Desist, the mystery drama Fortune Defies Death, and the drama P.T.S.D. He also plays piano professionally, providing musical accompaniment for Frank Sinatra Jr. in 2 episodes of The Defenders. He can be seen on the hit internet horror/comedy show The Vamps Next Door as Fred Peepers. He was awarded a top prize by the legendary Vincent Price for his poem \u201CHere Lies Madness,\u201D and later published a book by that name. Presently, Mr. Butler and his daughter Bonnie host a Movie Review called \u201CLittle Stinkers,\u201D on YouTube, in which they critique movies for young children. They also do a Vaudeville Song and Comedy Act in several venues in Los Angeles and on the internet. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(344, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(345, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(346, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(347, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(348, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(349, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(350, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(351, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(352, "img", 45);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(353, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(354, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(355, " We at Colorado Festival of Horror: Funhouse love a good slasher! So we\u2019re excited to announce 2 SPECIAL GUESTS Sarah French & Joe Knetter and a special DOUBLE-FEATURE slasher event Friday evening, Sept 9th starting at 7pm! Two films that feature a mask, creepier than the infamous Michael Myers\u2019 one! You\u2019ll meet the man behind the mask in-person, too, Jed Rowen. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(356, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(357, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(358, "\n7-9pm 2019\u2019s \u201CBlind\u201D\n");
        i0.ɵɵelement(359, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(360, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(361, "\n9-11pm 2021\u2019s \u201CPretty Boy\u201D ** COLORADO PREMIERE **\n");
        i0.ɵɵelement(362, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(363, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(364, "\nAnd the claw on this hammer, so to speak, are in-person Special Guests actor Sarah French and writer Joe Knetter! They will introduce the films and do a Q&A.\n");
        i0.ɵɵelement(365, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(366, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(367, "\nSarah French is an actress that has worked on a number of feature films, TV shows and music videos. Her horror/sci-fi credits include Blind, Pretty Boy, Space Hunters: The Battle for Deepstar, Death Count and The Special. She is an avid hiker and cross trains regularly. Her mantra is: \"If I'm not working on a project, I'm working on myself.\"\n");
        i0.ɵɵelement(368, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(369, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(370, "\nFrom a young age, Joe Knetter immersed himself in the horror genre, loving the feeling of being scared and creeped out. Lucky for him, the 80s were a powerhouse time for horror films with the advent of the home video market. He watched everything he could get his hands on, taking in the craft of proper storytelling. What Joe took from it was the feeling of making an impact and affecting people, something he's aimed to do with films like Blind, Pretty Boy, and Space Hunters: The Battle for Deepstar. He was also one of the writer's picked to finish George A. Romero's last zombie epic Twilight of the Dead. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(371, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(372, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(373, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(374, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(375, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(376, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(377, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(378, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(379, "img", 46);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(380, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(381, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(382, " \"Pretty Boy\" himself Jed Rowen will be joining Sarah French & Joe Knetter at Colorado Festival of Horror 2022: Funhouse! Jed will also be at our special DOUBLE-FEATURE slasher event Friday evening, Sept 9th starting at 7pm! ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(383, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(384, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(385, " 7-9pm 2019\u2019s \u201CBlind\u201D showing in the Circus of the Damned Video Room ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(386, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(387, " 9-11pm 2021\u2019s \u201CPretty Boy\u201D ** COLORADO PREMIERE ** showing in Monster Main Events ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(388, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(389, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(390, " Jed Rowen is an award-winning actor who\u2019s always up for a convention appearance and is thrilled to be going back to Colorado to attend yet another one! The Colorado Festival of Horror will be screening some of Jed\u2019s best work, the features Blind and the most recent, Pretty Boy, in which Jed plays the title role. Along with these two horror gems, a movie that screened way back in 2007 in Denver, Zombie Farm, is coming back from the dead in yet another incarnation at COFOH, this time entitled Pandemic Undead. Some of Jed\u2019s other notable credits over the years include Sluggo in The Ghastly Love of Johnny X and Det. Ray Garton in the notorious worldwide phenomenon Amazing Bulk. He\u2019s also very proud of recent roles in Space Hunters: The Battle for Deepstar, That\u2019s A Wrap and Area 5150. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(391, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(392, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(393, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(394, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(395, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(396, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(397, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(398, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(399, "img", 47);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(400, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(401, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(402, " Colorado Festival of Horror is thrilled to announce director/producer/actor Lloyd Kaufman, co-founder of Troma Entertainment, is coming to our September 2022 convention! Lloyd will be meeting fans, signing autographs and doing professional photo ops. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(403, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(404, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(405, "\nIn the late 1960s, Kaufman was enrolled at Yale University (where he would later present his Make Your Own Damn Movie Master Classes), diligently working on a respectable degree in Chinese Studies. However, Kaufman was destined for other things. As he explains in his hit book \u201CAll I Need To Know About Filmmaking I Learned From The Toxic Avenger\u201D (published by Penguin Putnam, and first of his seven books), \"At Yale, I was placed in a dormitory room with two film fanatics, and I knew everything had irrevocably changed.\" In fact, Kaufman was infected with a love of movies from which he never recovered. In 1971, Kaufman met his future partner Michael Herz at Yale. The Troma Universe was born in 1974 with a series of highly original, raunchy comedies such as Squeeze Play!, Stuck On You!, Waitress!, and other titles ending with an exclamation point. These movies, independent precursors to such later smash hits as National Lampoon's Animal House and Porky's, did well financially, although Kaufman continued to work on such outside productions as Rocky and Saturday Night Fever. Kaufman's relationship with mainstream Hollywood would not last long \"There were problems,\" Kaufman said \"I always wanted to do things my own way, and my employers insisted I do things the correct way.\" He continued to build up a list of impressive credits as well as some overpowering debts. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(406, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(407, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(408, "\nKaufman proved his former employers wrong with his 1984 breakthrough movie, The Toxic Avenger. This tale of a health club mop boy named Melvin who is transformed into a hideously deformed creature of superhuman size and strength struck a chord with audiences and critics alike, demonstrating that a large number of people were interested in seeing things done Kaufman's way. The Toxic Avenger led to an animated television series, Toxic Crusaders, action figures, different Marvel comic book titles, a hot sauce, etc. There were three sequels. The most recent film in the series is Citizen Toxie: The Toxic Avenger Part IV. Currently, The Toxic Avenger is being developed by Legendary Entertainment and their team as a big-budget Hollywood remake with Peter Dinklage, Elijah Wood and Kevin Bacon. Toxic Avenger The Musical is playing in London\u2019s West End, with music by Bon Jovi\u2019s David Bryan. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(409, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(410, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(411, "\nThe success of The Toxic Avenger was followed by a string of commercial and artistic triumphs in a similar vein, blending fantasy, heavy action, comedy, and eroticism in a style that can only be described as \"Tromatic\". These films, including the Class of Nuke \u2018Em High trilogy, Sgt. Kabukiman NYPD, and Troma's War, were often ignored or scorned by the intelligentsia of the time but spoke to an entire generation of young people who rejected the pandering, commercial films of the mid-to-late 80's. Some of these Troma fans went on to become filmmakers themselves, including Quentin Tarantino, Kevin Smith, Mike Judge, Peter Jackson, and Trey Parker. Thanks to these admirers, Kaufman has been asked to make cameo appearances in films like James Gunn\u2019s Guardians of the Galaxy, Sharknado 4, Trey Parker's Orgazmo, Eli Roth's Cabin Fever, and about 200 other indie movies. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(412, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(413, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(414, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(415, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(416, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(417, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(418, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(419, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(420, "img", 48);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(421, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(422, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(423, " Colorado Festival of Horror 2022: Funhouse is thrilled to announce actor/pro-wrestler/cosplayer Monique Dupree coming to our September 2022 convention! Monique will be meeting fans, signing autographs and doing professional photo ops. Newark, New Jersey native, Monique Dupree, is also known by the title Tha True Original Gata and in some circles, is referred to affectionately as The First Black Scream Queen. She was also The First Black \u201CTromette\u201D in many of Lloyd Kaufman\u2019s Troma Entertainment films. She has done independent horror films, comic-book, catalog and/or alternative modeling, local and national reality television and an occasional cross-over into mainstream television and cinema. Monique\u2019s most notable recent role was \u201CCaliban\u201D from Troma Entertainment\u2019s \u201C#Shakespeare\u2019s Shitstorm.\u201D She wears many hats including publishing, promotion, photography, internet radio, fitness, production and pro-wrestling. She tours behind the scenes and wrestles for former ECW star Tommy Dreamer in his promotion House of Hardcore as well as Impact Wrestling. Monique is also a professional Cosplayer appearing at events and conventions. The most notable cosplay to date being, Wonder Woman, Nubia, Mohawk Storm and Marie Antoinette. Monique has 10 children with her husband, author Anthony Saint Thomas. She is involved in several grass-root charities and social outreach organizations. Monique has completed upward of 100 films and television projects, inspired the creation of several comic-book heroines and consistently works and is for hire across the country and around the world. You Tube: Tha True Original Gata ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(424, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(425, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(426, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(427, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(428, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(429, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(430, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(431, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(432, "img", 49);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(433, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(434, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(435, " Colorado Festival of Horror 2022: Funhouse is thrilled to announce award-winning Special Guest Author Steve Rasnic Tem coming to our September 2022 convention on Saturday, September 10th! Steve will be meeting fans and signing books at the Hex Publishers table! Steve Rasnic Tem is a past winner of the Bram Stoker, World Fantasy, and British Fantasy Awards. His novel Ubo (Solaris Books), a finalist for the Bram Stoker Award, is a dark science fictional tale about violence and its origins, featuring such historical viewpoint characters as Jack the Ripper, Stalin, and Heinrich Himmler. He has published almost 500 short stories in his 40+ year career. Some of his best are collected in Thanatrauma and Figures Unseen from Valancourt Books. Steve also has the chilling short story \"Late Sleepers\" in Hex's It Came From the Multiplex: 80s Midnight Chillers anthology. The convention exclusive edition will be on sale at the show! Visit Steve's home on the web at ");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(436, "a", 50);
        i0.ɵɵtext(437, "www.stevetem.com");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(438, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(439, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(440, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(441, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(442, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(443, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(444, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(445, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(446, "img", 51);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(447, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(448, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(449, " Colleen Cole is an avid tabletop and PC gamer, model, sci-fi lover and comic enthusiast with a BA in Theatre. Colleen naturally gravitated to the world of cosplay almost ten years ago. You may remember her as Elvira and the Hellraiser Female Cenobite plus other favorite cosplays include Lady Death, Vampirella and Red Sonja. She's currently working on cosplays for the upcoming show plus Colleen will be a judge at our COFOH Gore Galore Costume Extravaganza at Colorado Festival of Horror Funhouse 2022! ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(450, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(451, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(452, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(453, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(454, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(455, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(456, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(457, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(458, "img", 52);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(459, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(460, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(461, " Colorado Festival of Horror is thrilled to announce actor Eugene Clark, \u201CBig Daddy\u201D himself from George A. Romero\u2019s \u201CLand of the Dead\u201D coming to our September 2022 convention! Eugene will be meeting fans, signing autographs and doing professional photo ops wearing the overalls and creepy contact lenses of \u201CBig Daddy\u201D! Eugene Clark brings a career in theater, television and film that is fascinating and diverse. A veteran of more than 100 television productions and 15 feature films, he won a Gemini Award (Canadian Emmy) for Best Supporting Actor in a Dramatic Series for his work on the hit TV series Night Heat. He starred as Mufasa in Disney's The Lion King onstage in Toronto for two years, as Horse in The Charlottetown Festival's production of The Full Monty in P.E.I., and starred as the lead zombie Big Daddy, in George A. Romero's long-awaited Land of the Dead. He has appeared in the films Trailer Park Boys: The Movie and Resurrecting the Champ and the TV series The L.A. Complex, Space Riders: Division Earth, The Latest Buzz, Sue Thomas: F.B.Eye, Wingin' It and The Line. He was the 2nd lead in William Shatner's made for television movie series TekWar. He received critical acclaim for his performance as a suicidal Vietnam veteran who lost his arm to Agent Orange in Unnatural Causes, the Emmy Award-winning drama starring John Ritter and Alfre Woodard. Acting is just one of Clark's creative outlets. Singing has long been a love in his life. From the days of singing as a child in his grandfather's church, to singing the national anthem in uniform as a member of the Toronto Argonauts, singing has always been \"like breath itself,\" he says. Distressed by television coverage of Africa's young famine victims, Clark wrote the lyrics, melody, and chorus to \u201CLetter from a Concerned Citizen (Starvation in Africa)\u201D. The Canadian Red Cross used the song for their national television and radio campaign to raise funds for their relief efforts in Africa. Of his three CDs he says, \"They speak to the need for effective community and global co-operation, how through assisting each other in times of need we can accomplish anything. These songs motivate and encourage us to be our best, for there is greatness in all of us.\u201D ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(462, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(463, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(464, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(465, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(466, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(467, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(468, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(469, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(470, "img", 53);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(471, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(472, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(473, " Colorado Festival of Horror is excited to announce local artist Joe Blablazo who has created art for the festival! Spewed forth from the hot sands of the southwest, Joe Blablazo has been drawing myths and monsters of all shapes and sizes for the last century. His adventures, seeking what cannot be found and knowing the unknowable, have found him showing work in flea markets, galleries, classrooms, comic cons, the world wide web, and BEYOND!! When he's not doing that he's been spotted in Colorado chilling out max and relaxing all cool. You\u2019ll be able to find his art on T-shirts, refrigerator magnets and posters for this year\u2019s Colorado Festival of Horror 2022: Funhouse event. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(474, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(475, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(476, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(477, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(478, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(479, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(480, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(481, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(482, "img", 54);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(483, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(484, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(485, " Damien Leone is an American Writer, Director, Producer and Special Effects Artist. Damien is best known for writing and directing the Horror film \u201CAll Hallows' Eve\u201D in 2013 when he introduced to the world to his unrelenting killer, \u201CArt the Clown.\u201D He has gone on to thrill horror fans and receive critical acclaim with the release of the film \u201CTerrifier\u201D establishing \u201CArt the Clown\u201D as a legend in the horror genre. The upcoming sequel, \u201CTerrifier 2\u201D which will be released in 2022. Damien\u2019s incredible Special Effects will also appear in the upcoming horror film \u201CStream.\u201D Damien resides in New York City. ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(486, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(487, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(488, "img", 55);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(489, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(490, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(491, " David Howard Thornton is an American actor originally from Huntsville, AL. Now based in New York City, he continues his stage, film, and voice over work. He is best known for his roles as \"Grandpa Who\" in the 1st to 5th national tours of \"Dr. Seuss' How the Grinch Stole Christmas: The Musical\", the voice of \"Shizoku\" and others in the video game \"Invizimals: The Lost Kingdom.\" David has also portrayed \"The Joker\" in the YouTube series, \"Nightwing Escalation.\" Most notably and to critical acclaim, David portrays \"Art the Clown\" in the horror film \"Terrifier\" and will reprise his role as \"Art\" in the upcoming sequel, \"Terrifier 2.\" David will also be seen in the upcoming films \"The Dark Offerings\" and \"Stream.\" ");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(492, "div", 20);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(493, "div", 21);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(494, "div", 22);
        i0.ɵɵelement(495, "img", 23);
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(496, "div", 24);
        i0.ɵɵelement(497, "p");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(498, "div", 12);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(499, "mat-card", 13);
        i0.ɵɵelement(500, "img", 56);
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(501, "mat-card-content");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(502, "p", 15);
        i0.ɵɵtext(503, " Denver - \u201CColorado Festival of Horror (COFOH) 2022: Funhouse\u201D returns for our second year September 9, 10, and 11, 2022, at the Embassy Suites by Hilton Denver Central Park, 4444 N. Havana St, Denver, CO 80239. COFOH is an intimate fan experience and convention for all things horror, featuring celebrity guests, artists, writers, vendors, panels and so much more. In that screaming tradition COFOH is proud to announce actress, producer and director Lynn Lowry of THE CRAZIES and SHIVERS fame! ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(504, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(505, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(506, " Lynn Lowry is an American born actress who\u2019s been performing, directing and producing for five decades. She is best known for the cult classic horror films, I DRINK YOUR BLOOD, THE CRAZIES, SHIVERS and CAT PEOPLE. But her professional career really began when at seventeen she acted opposite the sixteen-year-old John Belushi at the Shawnee Summer Theatre in Bloomfield, Indiana. Shortly after that Lynn went to New York where she starred opposite Peter Fonda in FIGHTING MAD directed by academy award winner, Jonathan Demme. She was a regular on the soap opera, HOW TO SURVIVE A MARRIAGE opposite F. Murray Abraham and Brad Davis and also acted in ANOTHER WORLD. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(507, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(508, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(509, " While in New York, Lynn studied all styles of theatre, becoming a producer and director at the Off-Broadway Theatre, The Production Company and did three plays at the famed Manhattan Theatre Club. In the past 20 years, Lynn has been singing with her jazz trio in Los Angeles and doing a multitude of Indy Films. She\u2019s won thirteen Best Actress Awards for her work in MODEL HUNGER, BASEMENT JACK, THE PERIPHERAL and READY FOR MY CLOSE-UP and three Lifetime Achievement Awards at various film festivals. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(510, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(511, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(512, " Lynn Lowry was very fortunate to have had the opportunity to work with George A. Romero, David Cronenberg, David E. Durston, Paul Schrader and many more wonderful directors. They provided her with a priceless legacy that will never die. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(513, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(514, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(515, " COFOH: Colorado Festival of Horror is preparing for its second-year event highlighting the horror genre, and all that it bleeds. ");
        i0.ɵɵelement(516, "br");
        i0.ɵɵelement(517, "br");
        i0.ɵɵtext(518, " COFOH will be a platform for the community to unite over the love of horror and everything that creeps in the night! For more information and event tickets visit us on our ");
        i0.ɵɵelementStart(519, "a", 37);
        i0.ɵɵtext(520, "Facebook Page.");
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
        i0.ɵɵelementEnd();
